div.div:
Precisions:
- All output need to be controlled by a esp32 which speaks on the canbus
- To total output of the regulator needs to be at least 10A and each channels needs to be able to handle 4A
- The total of all fuses right of the regulator must be lower than the rated current output
- The output cables needs to be ethernet connectors with the correct pinout (see elec. guidelines)
- The input is a XT-60 power connector
- Need to be stackable or stacked with a 20A connection between the XT60 and the stackable power sharing (see 10159561-200121RLF and 10159560-200421 for power sharing)
